member.name: P:Net.Client.ClientBase.HeartInterval
member.summary: 心跳时间间隔, 默认每1秒检查一次玩家是否离线, 玩家心跳确认为5次, 如果超出5次 则移除玩家客户端. 确认玩家离线总用时5秒, 如果设置的值越小, 确认的速度也会越快. 值太小有可能出现直接中断问题, 设置的最小值在100以上

summary.para: 心跳检测次数, 默认为5次检测, 如果5次发送心跳给客户端或服务器, 没有收到回应的心跳包, 则进入断开连接处理
当一直有数据往来时是不会发送心跳数据的, 只有当没有数据往来了, 才会进入发送心跳数据

member.name: F:Net.Client.ClientBase.operations
member.summary: 待发送的操作列表

summary.para: （Maxium Transmission Unit）最大传输单元, 最大传输单元为1500字节, 这里默认为50000, 如果数据超过50000,则是该框架进行分片. 传输层则需要分片为50000/1472=34个数据片
------ 局域网可以设置为50000, 公网需要设置为1300 或 1400, 如果设置为1400还是发送失败, 则需要设置为1300或以下进行测试 ------
1.链路层：以太网的数据帧的长度为(64+18)~(1500+18)字节，其中18是数据帧的帧头和帧尾，所以数据帧的内容最大为1500字节（不包括帧头和帧尾），即MUT为1500字节
2.网络层：IP包的首部要占用20字节，所以这里的MTU＝1500－20＝1480字节
3.传输层：UDP包的首部要占有8字节，所以这里的MTU＝1480－8＝1472字节

see.langword: 注意:服务器和客户端的MTU属性的值必须保持一致性,否则分包的数据将解析错误!

member.name: T:Net.Client.UdpClient
member.summary: Udp网络客户端 在安卓端必须设置可以后台运行, 如果不设置,当你按下home键后,app的所有线程将会被暂停,这会影响网络心跳检测线程,导致网络中断 解决方法 : 在android项目AndroidManifest.xml文件中的activity中添加如下内容： android:configChanges="fontScale|keyboard|keyboardHidden|locale|mnc|mcc|navigation|orientation|screenLayout|screenSize|smallestScreenSize|uiMode|touchscreen" 详情请看此博文:https://www.cnblogs.com/nanwei/p/9125316.html 或这个博文: http://www.voidcn.com/article/p-yakpcmce-bpk.html

member.name: T:Net.Server.ServerBase`2
member.summary:
网络服务器核心基类 2019.11.22
Player:当有客户端连接服务器就会创建一个Player对象出来, Player对象和XXXClient是对等端, 每当有数据处理都会通知Player对象.
Scene:你可以定义自己的场景类型, 比如帧同步场景处理, mmorpg场景什么处理, 可以重写Scene的Update等等方法实现每个场景的更新和处理.

member.summary: 心跳时间间隔, 默认每2秒检查一次玩家是否离线, 玩家心跳确认为5次, 如果超出5次 则移除玩家客户端. 确认玩家离线总用时10秒, 如果设置的值越小, 确认的速度也会越快. 但发送的数据也会增加. [开发调式时尽量把心跳值设置高点]

summary.para: 心跳检测次数, 默认为5次检测, 如果5次发送心跳给客户端或服务器, 没有收到回应的心跳包, 则进入断开连接处理
当一直有数据往来时是不会发送心跳数据的, 只有当没有数据往来了, 才会进入发送心跳数据

summary.para: （Maxium Transmission Unit）最大传输单元, 最大传输单元为1500字节
1.链路层：以太网的数据帧的长度为(64+18)~(1500+18)字节，其中18是数据帧的帧头和帧尾，所以数据帧的内容最大为1500字节（不包括帧头和帧尾），即MUT为1500字节
2.网络层：IP包的首部要占用20字节，所以这里的MTU＝1500－20＝1480字节
3.传输层：UDP包的首部要占有8字节，所以这里的MTU＝1480－8＝1472字节

see.langword: 注意:服务器和客户端的MTU属性的值必须保持一致性,否则分包的数据将解析错误!

member.summary: Indicates the status code for the WebSocket connection close.

remarks.para:
The values of this enumeration are defined in
Section 7.4 of RFC 6455.
"Reserved value" cannot be sent as a status code in closing handshake by an endpoint.

member.name: F:UnityWebSocket.CloseStatusCode.Normal
member.summary: Equivalent to close status 1000. Indicates normal close.

member.name: F:UnityWebSocket.CloseStatusCode.Away
member.summary: Equivalent to close status 1001. Indicates that an endpoint is going away.

member.name: F:UnityWebSocket.CloseStatusCode.ProtocolError
member.summary: Equivalent to close status 1002. Indicates that an endpoint is terminating the connection due to a protocol error.

member.name: F:UnityWebSocket.CloseStatusCode.UnsupportedData
member.summary: Equivalent to close status 1003. Indicates that an endpoint is terminating the connection because it has received a type of data that it cannot accept.

member.name: F:UnityWebSocket.CloseStatusCode.Undefined
member.summary: Equivalent to close status 1004. Still undefined. A Reserved value.

member.name: F:UnityWebSocket.CloseStatusCode.NoStatus
member.summary: Equivalent to close status 1005. Indicates that no status code was actually present. A Reserved value.

member.name: F:UnityWebSocket.CloseStatusCode.Abnormal
member.summary: Equivalent to close status 1006. Indicates that the connection was closed abnormally. A Reserved value.

member.name: F:UnityWebSocket.CloseStatusCode.InvalidData
member.summary: Equivalent to close status 1007. Indicates that an endpoint is terminating the connection because it has received a message that contains data that is not consistent with the type of the message.

member.name: F:UnityWebSocket.CloseStatusCode.PolicyViolation
member.summary: Equivalent to close status 1008. Indicates that an endpoint is terminating the connection because it has received a message that violates its policy.

member.name: F:UnityWebSocket.CloseStatusCode.TooBig
member.summary: Equivalent to close status 1009. Indicates that an endpoint is terminating the connection because it has received a message that is too big to process.

member.name: F:UnityWebSocket.CloseStatusCode.MandatoryExtension
member.summary: Equivalent to close status 1010. Indicates that a client is terminating the connection because it has expected the server to negotiate one or more extension, but the server did not return them in the handshake response.

member.name: F:UnityWebSocket.CloseStatusCode.ServerError
member.summary: Equivalent to close status 1011. Indicates that a server is terminating the connection because it has encountered an unexpected condition that prevented it from fulfilling the request.

member.name: F:UnityWebSocket.CloseStatusCode.TlsHandshakeFailure
member.summary: Equivalent to close status 1015. Indicates that the connection was closed due to a failure to perform a TLS handshake. A Reserved value.
